{"id":789,"date":"2009-03-13T06:43:14","date_gmt":"2009-03-13T11:43:14","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/a_bright_new_day_for_dia.php"},"modified":"2009-03-13T06:43:14","modified_gmt":"2009-03-13T11:43:14","slug":"a_bright_new_day_for_dia","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/a_bright_new_day_for_dia.php","title":{"rendered":"A Bright New Day for Dia"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/dia_logo.gif\" alt=\"Dia Logo, Before and After\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Short for Distribuidora Internacional de Alimentacion (roughly <em>International Provision Distributor<\/em>), <a href=\"http:\/\/www.dia.es\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Dia<\/a> is a Carrefour-owned, hard-discount grocery store &mdash; meaning, from what I understand, that they can reduce costs wildly by minimizing operations and simplifying their stores &mdash; with a vast presence in Spain with more than 2,900 stores and can also be found around the world in Greece, Turkey, Argentina, Brazil, and China. Last year, <a href=\"http:\/\/www.interbrand.com\/case_study.aspx?caseid=1114&#038;langid=1000\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Interbrand redesigned a new identity for Dia<\/a>, replacing the generic but oh-so-European-looking Avant Garde with a custom lettering wordmark, and in recent months stores have been upgraded to the new look and store design. I really like the new logo, the letterforms are very well integrated and resolved, the &#8220;a&#8221; is downright great and I will even let go of the missing tittle (<a href=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/archives\/financial_services_period.php#467223\">thanks for the term Mike<\/a>), because in this case it does reflect positively on the overall shape. You can see some images of the stores <a href=\"http:\/\/www.diacorporate.com\/diawebapp\/web\/external-relations\/photo-gallery.jsp\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">at Dia&#8217;s corporate web site<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p><span class=\"small\"><strong>Thanks to <a href=\"http:\/\/www.reyarts.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Romeo Calonghi<\/a> for the tip.<\/strong><\/span><\/p>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<img src=\"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/images\/excerpt_empty.gif\" alt=\"Excerpt Empty\" \/>","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"episode_type":"","audio_file":"","duration":"","filesize":"","date_recorded":"","explicit":"","block":"","filesize_raw":""},"categories":[9,86,26],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/789"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=789"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/789\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=789"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=789"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.underconsideration.com\/brandnew\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=789"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}